about.summary: Create preliminary exploratory data visualisations of an entire  dataset to identify problems or unexpected features using 'ggplot2'.

name: r-visdat
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-visdat
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/visdat_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/visdat/visdat_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 527c76b6643b8475a58516763ef40238cdc61ec62d2dcf690f7c316b93b878c6

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('visdat')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('visdat')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://visdat.njtierney.com/, https://github.com/ropensci/visdat
  license: MIT
  summary: Create preliminary exploratory data visualisations of an entire  dataset to identify problems or unexpected features using 'ggplot2'.
  license_family: MIT

  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
